{
  "skillId": "distribute-negative-multiplier",
  "atomType": "R",
  "theory": {
    "intro": "When the term in front of a bracket is negative, you still multiply it by every term inside — but the negative multiplier changes the sign of each product. Getting the sign of each term right is the whole skill.",
    "facts": [
      "The distributive law still applies: $-a(b+c) = -ab - ac$ — the negative outside multiplies **every** term inside.",
      "Use the sign rule on each product: a negative times a **positive** is **negative**, a negative times a **negative** is **positive**.",
      "A subtraction inside is a negative term: $-3(2x-5)$ means $-3 \\times 2x$ and $-3 \\times (-5) = +15$, so the sign **flips**.",
      "A bare minus in front, like $-(x-3)$, means multiply by $-1$: every sign inside flips."
    ],
    "steps": [
      "Multiply each inside term by the outside term.",
      "Apply the sign rule to each product.",
      "Write the expanded expression."
    ]
  },
  "practice": {
    "foundation": [
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-2(x+4)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-2(x+4)$\n$= -2(x) - 2(4)$\n$= -2x-8$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-4(3b+2)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-4(3b+2)$\n$= -4(3b) - 4(2)$\n$= -12b-8$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-3(x-2)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-3(x-2)$\n$= -3(x) - 3(-2)$\n$= -3x+6$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-(x-3)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-(x-3)$\n$= -1(x) - 1(-3)$\n$= -x+3$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-4(3-x)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-4(3-x)$\n$= -4(3) - 4(-x)$\n$= -12+4x$"
      }
    ],
    "development": [
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-3(2x-5)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-3(2x-5)$\n$= -3(2x) - 3(-5)$\n$= -6x+15$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-5(2x+3)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-5(2x+3)$\n$= -5(2x) - 5(3)$\n$= -10x-15$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-6(3-e)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-6(3-e)$\n$= -6(3) - 6(-e)$\n$= -18+6e$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-(4x-9)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-(4x-9)$\n$= -1(4x) - 1(-9)$\n$= -4x+9$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-7y(4x+7)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-7y(4x+7)$\n$= -7y(4x) - 7y(7)$\n$= -28xy-49y$"
      }
    ],
    "mastery": [
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-2a(3a-1)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-2a(3a-1)$\n$= -2a(3a) - 2a(-1)$\n$= -6a^2+2a$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-3y(4-5y)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-3y(4-5y)$\n$= -3y(4) - 3y(-5y)$\n$= -12y+15y^2$"
      },
      {
        "question_text": "Expand $-2(4x-3y+5)$.",
        "solution_text": "$-2(4x-3y+5)$\n$= -2(4x) - 2(-3y) - 2(5)$\n$= -8x+6y-10$"
      }
    ]
  }
}
